result.adr_address: 49 Peel St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Peel Fresco Music Lounge

reviews.text: Love this place! Went there first time for Sibel’s Jazz concert. Stayed for almost 2 hours with good music, nice atmosphere, and some drinks. And keep going back ever since! Entrance is 100 which is a really good deal!
I'd give it 5 stars if the smashingly irresponsible hellion I planned to meet here hadn't fled into the night (with her father in tow) mere minutes before my arrival. Cozy spot though.
First time checking out a jazz cafe in Hong Kong. Very impressed with the place . The atmosphere is very calming and the music and performers speak English well and can play very good.
If you love music, here is fine. But too close to other customer. No place to dance. And single customer may not be enjoyable because bar counter is located very much inside.
Cool place to hang out for drinks and the live band, Glen Alfred was good.
